INSERT INTO `craft_searchindex` (`elementId`, `attribute`, `fieldId`, `locale`, `keywords`) VALUES ('12', 'field', '2', 'en_us', ' nicole jones wrote an article called editing the past last february and i ve been thinking about it ever since it s a strange little piece with nearly every sentence a question but it has a persistent idea now that we have hundreds of posts over a span of years what do we do with them i had already been asking myself a similar question after blogging for a few years i have a handful of posts i m really proud of so what s the best way to present the writing nicole s barrage of questions broke free an idea for me which is to create a page of evergreen content structured like a magazine that features all of my best articles this is finally a reality in brianfeeney us v6 i like the idea of a living magazine something that can be updated when i ve learned something new or if the world changes in a significant way the internet allows for an entirely different kind of evergreen content content that might not be timeless from the start but which could become so with a little pruning of the leaves this kind of writing allows for spontaneity and immediacy but frees me from the stigma of editing old blog posts mandy brown has a version of this at a working library a really lovely site i m don t plan on having a blog again i m happy with just a collection of articles i ll tweet about newly posted writing when it happens and i ll highlight old articles if i feel like it but for now look around and see if there s something you ve not yet seen this feels to me like a project other people could and should jump on board with it s an open idea similar to fictive kin s purpose which is wonderfully effective and complete i would absolutely love to see an evergreen page from my favorite bloggers like frank chimero etc but until they create one here s mine ');
